description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

description: Monthly registered beginner salsa fundamentals class
Monthly registered beginner–intermediate salsa class
Monthly registered intermediate–advanced salsa class

Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha- Beginner Intermediate
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

dance_style: bachata, cha cha, dance, merengue, salsa
description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open
Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson
Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight
Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: STUDIO 4 ATHLETICS, 715 YATES ST, Langley, BC, CA

After the class, enjoy an open-air social featuring a dynamic blend of Salsa, Bachata, and Kizomba, with just a light touch of Merengue to round out the evening. This is a beautiful, inclusive, and supportive community where new friendships are made and everyone belongs.
location: Songhees Plaza (near the Johnson Street Bridge), 30 Esquimalt Rd, Victoria, BC V9A, Canada
price: $5 for students (with valid ID), $10 general admission

Sponsored by the City of Victoria.

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Get ready to dance, groove, and celebrate at ArtisTREE Festival 2025, where the music is as diverse and joyful as the community it brings together! Taking place July 26–27 on the stunning grounds of Government House, this free, all-ages outdoor festival invites you to move your body and lift your spirits with a lineup that’s bursting with rhythm and soul. This year’s musical menu features everything from high-energy Afro-Latin fusion with crowd favourite TK The Artist, to the raw power of Indigenous hip hop by PINDN, and the uplifting global beats of Bopoma and Nostic. Families will love the joyful performances by Mister Mojo, while dancers of all kinds can jump into a public swing dance lesson with Red Hot Swing, a Rueda salsa circle with UVic’s Salsa Club, or even a full-on square dance with The Slieves. Plus: the lush, percussive grooves of the Miguelito Valdés Trio, the retro jazz charm of the Capital City Syncopators, and an open marimba jam you won’t want to miss. Whether you come to move, listen, or simply soak up the energy, ArtisTREE’s music lineup is your invitation to celebrate creativity, culture, and community together.
location: Government House Gardens, 1401 Rockland Ave, Victoria, BC, Canada

description: Free Dance Lessons and Dance Shows The Sunday Afternoon Salsa dances start with a free beginner salsa dance lesson at 3pm for anyone who has ever wanted to learn how to dance salsa, even those who claim they have two left feet! The lesson lasts for half an hour (3:00-3:30pm) and is taught by Baza Dance Studios. At 5pm there are dance performances by local dancers and dance companies representing a wide variety of different dance styles. This week’s show will be by Salsa Caliente! The Sunday Afternoon Salsa dances are open to everyone and you are welcome even if you’ve never danced a day in your life.
location: 1030 Robson ST, VANCOUVER, BC, V6E1A7, CA
